  "texts": [
    "We see very few edge weights less than or equal to 0 that will be removed by thresholding.",
    "This indicates that conditioned on co-occurring at least once, two terms are likely to co-occur more often than would be expected by chance.",
    "In our experiments we found slightly better results using the NPMI edge weights.",
    "Community MiningOnce the co-occurrence network is constructed, CT discovers topics by applying a community detection method.A community is a group of vertices that have a greater density of connections among themselves than they do to vertices outside the group.",
    "Many community detection algoritms exist and have been surveryed in other papers such as [17,25,26] or [74]."
